&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Fertility Nurse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an experienced Fertility nurse? If so, an exciting opportunity has arisen for a motivated and exceptional nurse with a strong background in Fertility. You will work in collaboration with professionals within the hospital setting to give appropriate specialist advice; support and education in relation to all aspects of fertility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will provide clinical leadership, promote excellence in nursing practice and be able to work across organisational boundaries. You will also have the ability to provide guidance, supervision and training to peers and junior members of the team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like to know more please contact Michael Jones, Matron for Theatres, Fertility and Procedures – &lt;span&gt;Michael.jones18@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt; or 0121 471 5472. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be held week commencing 16&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
